    "Second, examination performance in and of itself provides little information regarding the potential of models to contribute to clinical practice as a medical-assistance tool [3].",
    "Clinical benchmarks are required to understanding the meaning and implications of scores in ophthalmological examinations attained by LLMs and are a necessary precursor to clinical trials of LLM-based interventions.",
    "Here, we used FRCOphth Part 2 examination questions to gauge the ophthalmological knowledge base and reasoning capability of LLMs using fully qualified and currently training ophthalmologists as clinical benchmarks.",
    "These questions were not freely available online, minimising the risk of contamination.",
    "The FRCOphth Part 2 Written Examination tests the clinical knowledge and skills of ophthalmologists in training using multiple choice questions with no negative marking and must be passed to fully qualify as a specialist eye doctor in the United Kingdom."
  ],
